<div id="pf567a" class="pf w43 h34e" data-page-no="567a"><div class="pc pc567a w43 h34e"><div class="t m78e x26 h73 y3247 ff3 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Overshadowing Providence </div><div class="t m5 x8f h73 y31dc ff3 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mab9 xbb h73 y3247 ff3 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">March 30 </div><div class="t m9b8 x11 h22 y2f67 ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">10. Read 2 Samuel 22:35-43 in light of the principles of the great </div><div class="t m140 x74 h22 y2f0e ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">controversy between Christ and Satan. (See Rev. 12:1-17.) How </div><div class="t m90 x74 h22 y2d11 ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">would you explain the following? </div><div class="t m1fe x5d h28 y2a5f ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;He teaches my hands to make war&quot; (2 Sam. 22:35, NKJV; see Eph. </div><div class="t mbb2 x11 h28 y2b49 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6:10-17). </div><div class="t m34f x73 h28 y2190 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;You have subdued . . . those who rose against me&quot; (2 Sam. 22:40, </div><div class="t m5c5 x11 h28 y20bb ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NKJV; see Rev. 12:9-11). </div><div class="t m497 x73 h28 y1e5e ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;I beat them as fine as the dust of the earth&quot; (2 Sam. 22:43, NKJV; </div><div class="t m42f x11 h28 y1edf ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">see Ps. 2:8, 9; Rev. 19:15). </div><div class="t m3d9 xd0 h55 y1025 ff3 fs8 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">WED </div><div class="t md06 x11 h22 yad0 ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">11. Summarize in your own words some of the reasons David had </div><div class="t m5c5 x61 h22 y81f ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for being grateful: </div><div class="t m7fe x64 h28 y18ee ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2 Sam. 22:20, 44 </div><div class="t m5 x6b h28 y18ee ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m726 x179 h28 y18ee ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t mb5 x64 h28 ybb3 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 26-28 </div><div class="t m5 x7c h28 ybb3 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m726 x1d3 h28 ybb3 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t md30 x64 h28 y24a ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 29-31 </div><div class="t m5 x7c h28 y981 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m726 x1d3 h28 y981 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m149a x64 h28 y1a1 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 36, 37 </div><div class="t m5 x7c h28 y1a1 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m726 x1d3 h28 y1a1 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m1db x64 h28 y1c86 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 50, 51 </div><div class="t m5 x7c h28 y1c86 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m726 x1d3 h28 y1c86 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m874 x48 h28 yf3d ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Deitrich Bonhoeffer, who spent the last years of his life in a Nazi prison </div><div class="t m319 x17 h28 y90a ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">camp and eventually became a martyr, loved and read the psalms daily. A </div><div class="t m698 x17 h28 y17fa ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">friend who was with him in his last days said that he seemed to diffuse </div><div class="t mf36 x17 h28 y17a2 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">happiness and joy to those about him, and manifested a deep sense of grati-</div><div class="t m4ce x17 h28 y643 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tude over just being alive. He had learned well the lesson of the psalmist: </div><div class="t m1322 x17 h28 y1a3b ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">gratitude born of adversity sings God&apos;s praises from the heart, not just with </div><div class="t m77a x17 h28 y1b53 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the lips. </div><div class="t m3f2 x17 h22 y9e8 ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">IV. DAVID THE PROPHET (2 Sam. 23:1-7). </div><div class="t m453 x3e h22 y1c97 ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">12. </div><div class="t m92 x64 h22 y1c97 ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What New Testament criteria confirms David&apos;s prophetic gift? </div><div class="t m751 x64 h22 y11bc ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Who was the &quot;Rock of Israel&quot; who spoke to him (2 Sam. 23:1-</div><div class="t mea5 x64 h22 y167d ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3)? 2 Peter 1:21; 1 Cor. 10:4. </div><div class="t m453 x3e h22 y128e ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">13. </div><div class="t m8a0 x64 h22 y128e ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Study the following sampling of the prophecies made by David </div><div class="t m580 x64 h22 y5e9 ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">about the Messiah to come. Compare their New Testament fulfill-</div><div class="t m1322 x64 h22 y144 ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ment. </div><div class="t m2a4 x195 h22 y12c4 ff1 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">95 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
